---
description: Run or open the Ocean orchestrator CLI in this repo
globs: []
alwaysApply: false
---

When the user asks to run, open, or start **Ocean**, use the npm-installed CLI from the **repository root**:

1. Run `npm install` if `node_modules/` is missing or `package.json` / lockfile changed.
2. Run **`npx ocean`** (or **`npm start`**) plus any flags/subcommands they asked for (e.g. `npx ocean chat`, `npx ocean --help`).

Do not assume `ocean` is on the shell PATH unless they installed globally (`npm install -g .`). Prefer **`npx ocean`** for clones.
